title.narrative: Output 2.2: HEALTH “By 2022, National capacity for quality assurance of primary and secondary maternal, neonatal, child and adolescent health (MNCHA) services is strengthened.”

description.narrative: National capacity to deliver integrated maternal and child health services was increased through the following: capacity-building of health managers and service providers, an upgraded health information system, an improved supply chain of essential commodities, and community engagement. UNICEF intervention in nine targeted districts, populated by many of the poorest families, resulted in a threefold increase in the utilization of essential services – in absolute numbers, 299,430 families were reached with health and nutrition communication messages through individual counselling, and 534,374 live births took place in health facilities technically and financially supported through UNICEF programmes. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/12/2019
